Human Capital Management: 

It refers to a strategic approach to manage people (ie., employees) to valuable assets to maximise business values

HCM goes beyond basic HR tasks â€” it includes everything from hiring and training to performance management, compensation, and workforce planning.

ðŸ“¦ Key Components of HCM:
Workforce Planning - Forecasting hiring needs and aligning talent with goals
Talent Acquisition - Recruiting, selecting, and onboarding new employees
Learning & Development - Training, upskilling, and reskilling workforce
Performance Management - Setting goals, giving feedback, and conducting appraisals
Compensation & Benefits - Managing pay, incentives, and employee rewards
Succession Planning -	Identifying and preparing future leaders
HR Analytics - Using data to make informed HR decisions

